 {"id":"bd-3gmj","title":"Idempotency registry: safe retries for distributed operations","description":"# Idempotency Registry Implementation

## Goal

Implement an idempotency system that makes distributed operations safe to retry, enabling at-least-once delivery with at-most-once semantics.

## Background

Network failures require retries, but naive retries can cause duplicate effects:
- Double-charging a payment
- Sending duplicate messages
- Creating duplicate records

Idempotency tokens solve this: each operation has a unique ID, and repeated requests with the same ID return the cached result.

## Core Types

### IdempotencyToken
```rust
pub struct IdempotencyToken {
    /// Unique operation identifier
    id: OperationId,

    /// Requesting node
    origin: NodeId,

    /// Timestamp for expiry
    created_at: LogicalTime,

    /// Hash of request parameters (for validation)
    request_hash: u64,
}
```

### IdempotencyRecord
```rust
pub struct IdempotencyRecord {
    token: IdempotencyToken,

    /// Current state
    state: IdempotencyState,

    /// Cached result (if completed)
    result: Option<Vec<u8>>,

    /// When to expire this record
    expires_at: LogicalTime,
}

pub enum IdempotencyState {
    /// Operation in progress
    InProgress,

    /// Operation completed successfully
    Completed,

    /// Operation failed (cached error)
    Failed,

    /// Operation was cancelled
    Cancelled,
}
```

## IdempotencyRegistry

```rust
pub struct IdempotencyRegistry {
    /// All tracked operations
    records: HashMap<OperationId, IdempotencyRecord>,

    /// Expiry configuration
    config: IdempotencyConfig,

    /// Background cleanup task
    cleanup_task: TaskHandle,
}

impl IdempotencyRegistry {
    /// Check if operation was already performed
    fn check(&self, token: &IdempotencyToken) -> IdempotencyStatus;

    /// Start tracking a new operation
    fn begin(&mut self, token: IdempotencyToken) -> Result<(), IdempotencyError>;

    /// Record successful completion
    fn complete<R: Serialize>(&mut self, token: &IdempotencyToken, result: &R);

    /// Record failure
    fn fail(&mut self, token: &IdempotencyToken, error: &Error);

    /// Record cancellation
    fn cancel(&mut self, token: &IdempotencyToken);
}

pub enum IdempotencyStatus {
    /// Never seen this token
    New,

    /// Operation in progress
    InProgress,

    /// Already completed (here's the result)
    AlreadyCompleted(Vec<u8>),

    /// Already failed (here's the error)
    AlreadyFailed(Error),

    /// Request hash doesn't match (parameter mismatch)
    ParameterMismatch,
}
```

## Token Generation

```rust
impl IdempotencyToken {
    /// Generate a new unique token
    pub fn new(cx: &Cx) -> Self {
        Self {
            id: cx.random_u128().into(),
            origin: cx.node_id(),
            created_at: cx.logical_now(),
            request_hash: 0,  // Set by caller
        }
    }

    /// Create token with request hash
    pub fn for_request<R: Hash>(cx: &Cx, request: &R) -> Self {
        let mut token = Self::new(cx);
        token.request_hash = hash(request);
        token
    }
}
```

## Request Hash Validation

The request_hash ensures the same token is only valid for the same request:
- Same token + same parameters = return cached result
- Same token + different parameters = ParameterMismatch error

This catches bugs where tokens are reused incorrectly.

## Expiry and Cleanup

Records must be cleaned up eventually:
```rust
pub struct IdempotencyConfig {
    /// How long to keep completed records
    completed_ttl: Duration,

    /// How long to keep failed records
    failed_ttl: Duration,

    /// Max records to store
    max_records: usize,

    /// Cleanup interval
    cleanup_interval: Duration,
}
```

## Integration with Remote Spawn

```rust
// Idempotent remote spawn
async fn remote_spawn_idempotent<T: RemoteTask>(
    cx: &mut Cx,
    node: NodeId,
    task: T,
    token: IdempotencyToken,
) -> Result<RemoteHandle<T::Output>, Error> {
    match cx.idempotency().check(&token) {
        IdempotencyStatus::New => {
            cx.idempotency().begin(token.clone())?;
            let handle = remote_spawn(cx, node, task).await?;
            cx.idempotency().complete(&token, &handle.task_id);
            Ok(handle)
        }
        IdempotencyStatus::AlreadyCompleted(bytes) => {
            // Reconstruct handle from cached task_id
            let task_id: RemoteTaskId = deserialize(&bytes)?;
            Ok(RemoteHandle::from_existing(task_id))
        }
        // ... other cases
    }
}
```

## Testing

- New operation tracked correctly
- Retry returns cached result
- Parameter mismatch detected
- Expiry cleans up old records
- Concurrent retries handled correctly

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] IdempotencyToken with all fields
- [ ] IdempotencyRecord with state tracking
- [ ] IdempotencyRegistry with full API
- [ ] Token generation with node ID
- [ ] Request hash validation
- [ ] Expiry configuration
- [ ] Background cleanup task
